I"E<p>Memory can be seen as the <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/perception-is-context-dependent">perception</a> of <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/memory-is-like-a-manuscript">structural neural artifacts</a> caused by previous experience. This further <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/experiential-consequences-of-cognitivism">disconnects</a> the <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/mindfulness-breaks-self-induced-behaviors">self</a> from <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/world-image-is-a-chicken-egg-problem">the world</a>.</p>
